her. Culturally, France is recognized as the home of Marten Yorgantz, a popular singer, and it has been a significant hub for research and development, including the advancement of tanks during World War I. These various aspects collectively underscore France's prominence in sports, history, culture, and geography.\n\nFrance is also a country where the Nord Department is located and where Joe Ekins served as a tank gunner during World War II. Its industrial regions were targeted by the German Army during the invasion. The country has also been a significant site for the conflict between the Roman Catholic Church and Freemasonry. France signed the Treaty of Amiens with Britain in 1802, ending the Revolutionary Wars. It is one of the countries involved in the international co-production of Tiffany Memorandum, where the film is known as \"Coup de force \u00e0 Berlin.\" Turner Classic Movies is available in France, and the country was the first to screen \"The Art of Negative Thinking\" in the CineNordica program in Paris. Additionally, France is the country where G\u00e9vaudan was located and where the French Revolution took place. The Embassy of France represents the country in the United Kingdom. Maurice Fernez lived and worked in France.\n\nFrance is the country for which Jir\u00e8s Kembo Ekoko was a former youth international. It is also the country where Aldi Nord operates under the name Aldi March\u00e9 with 891 outlets. France is one of the settings of the novel Indiana. Additionally, France is the country where Charleville and the Ardennes department are located. It is also the country where Raymond Abescat was recognized as the oldest living man and veteran. Furthermore, France is the country where English Freemasonry spread to in the 1720s.<SEP>France is a country that officially recognizes French as its sole official language.<SEP>France is one of the primary nations involved in the Seven Years' War.<SEP>France has the second highest birth rate in the European Union with 13.013 births per thousand people per year.<SEP>France is the winning team of the 2018 FIFA World Cup.<SEP>France is a country where Aldi Nord operates under the name Aldi March\u00e9 with 899 outlets."}
